claim.claim-text:
26. The system of claim 3, wherein the additional tests of the first type are performed, failures in the at least one semiconductor device are re-identified and a number of re-identified types of failures are determined, with the decision circuitry subsequently: 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for the additional procedure when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a fourth number set; 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for repair when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a fifth number set; and 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for the additional tests of the first type when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a sixth number set; 
wherein the decision circuitry repeats such designations until alternately the number of the re-identified types of failures is within the fourth number set, the at least one semiconductor device is repairable and the number of the re-identified types of failures is within the fifth number set, or the additional tests of the first type have been performed a predetermined number of times and the number of re-identified types of failures is within the sixth number set.

28. The system of claim 26, wherein the additional procedure designated by the decision circuitry includes: 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for tests of a second type to the re-identify types of failures in the at least one semiconductor device and determine the number of re-identified types of failures; 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for a further procedure when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a seventh number set; 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for repair when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within an eighth number set; and 
the testing apparatus performing additional tests of the second type on the at least one semiconductor device when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a ninth number set.

32. A system for testing at least one semiconductor device comprising: 
apparatus for performing tests of a first type on the at least one semiconductor device, for identifying at least two types of failures in the at least one semiconductor device, and for determining at least one failure of a number of the identified at least two types of failures, the test apparatus performing: 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for an additional procedure when the number of the identified at least two types of failures is within a first number set; 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for repair when the number of the identified at least two types of failures is within a second number set; 
determining when the at least one semiconductor device is repairable; and 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for additional tests of the first type when the number of the identified at least two types of failures is within a third number set.

35. A method for a plurality of semiconductor devices comprising: 
utilizing a processing circuitry for performing tests of a first type on said semiconductor devices to identify types of failures in the at least one semiconductor device; 
determining a number of the identified types of failures; 
designating a semiconductor device having at least one identified type of failure for an additional procedure when the number of the identified types of failures is within a first number set; 
determining if the number of the identified types of failures is within a second number set; 
repairing the semiconductor device when the number of the identified types of failures is within the second number set; 
performing other tests of the first type on the semiconductor device when the number of the identified types of failures is within a third number set; and 
determining when a semiconductor device of the plurality of semiconductor devices is repairable.

36. The method of claim 35, wherein the other tests of the first type are performed, types of failures in the semiconductor device are re-identified and a number of re-identified types of failures is determined, further comprising: 
designating a semiconductor device being ready for the additional procedure when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a fourth number set; 
repairing the semiconductor device when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a fifth number set; and 
performing the other tests of the first type on the semiconductor device when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a sixth number set; 
wherein said designating, repairing, and performing are repeated until one of the number of the re-identified types of failures is within the fourth number set, the semiconductor device is repairable and the number of the re-identified types of failures is within the fifth number set, and the additional tests of the first type have been performed a predetermined number of times and the number of re-identified types of failures is within the sixth number set.

38. The method of claim 36, wherein the additional procedure includes: 
performing tests of a second type on the semiconductor device re-identifying types of failures in the semiconductor device and determining a number of types of re-identified failures; 
designating the at least one semiconductor device for a further procedure when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a seventh number set; 
repairing the semiconductor device when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within an eighth number set; and 
performing additional tests of the second type on the semiconductor device when the number of the re-identified types of failures is within a ninth number set.
